PARAM HANS YADAV & SADANAND TRIPATHI V. STATE OF BIHAR & ORS [1987] INSC 64; AIR 1987 SC 955; 1987 (2) SCR 405; 1987 (2) SCC 197; 1987 (1) JT 595; 1987 (1) SCALE 426 (25 February 1987)

 MISRA RANGNATH MISRA RANGNATH DUTT, M.M. (J) 
CITATION: 1987 AIR 955 1987 SCR (2) 405 1987 SCC (2) 197 JT 1987 (1) 595 1987 SCALE (1)426 
ACT:
 Indian Evidence Act, 1872:ss.24 & 30--Confession of a co-accused--Not Substantive evidence against other co- accused in the trial--Can be used only for lending assurance to other substantive evidence--Extra-judicial confession made following assault--Neither voluntary nor natural.
 Indian Penal Code, 1860:s.302 read with s. 120-B--Death sentence-Direct evidence--Accused caught red-handed--Con- fessed to his crime--Conviction and sentence upheld--Crime whether committed at the behest of co-accused--Where prose- cution relies upon circumstantial evidence a clear link to be established and the chain completed to prove conspiracy.
 
